cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.MM

The paper focuses on event detection from social media streams using both textual and image information. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves image analysis. The paper also involves statistical analysis and unsupervised machine learning, which falls under social and information networks (cs.SI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) categories. Information retrieval (cs.IR) is also a possible category as the paper deals with detecting events from large amounts of data. Finally, multimedia (cs.MM) is another possible category as the paper involves analyzing both text and images.
